data.meta_description: The WGA reached a tentative agreement with the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers on a new three-year Minimum Basic Agreement.
data.text:
148 Days Stronger

Across picket lines from Los Angeles to New York, the WGA fought for a fair deal and won, helping to inspire a new labor movement in Hollywood and around the world. Check out images and voices from the 148 day-long strike.
